Template: atom-heratio/install-mode
Type: select
Choices: complete, atom-only, heratio-only
Default: complete
Description: Installation mode:
 Choose how to install AtoM Heratio:
 .
  complete     - Extract bundled AtoM 2.10 + install Heratio framework
                 and all plugins (recommended for new installations)
 .
  atom-only    - Extract bundled AtoM 2.10 only (vanilla AtoM, no Heratio)
 .
  heratio-only - Detect existing AtoM (>= 2.8) and layer Heratio on top
                 (for existing AtoM installations)

Template: atom-heratio/atom-path
Type: string
Default: /usr/share/nginx/atom
Description: AtoM installation path:
 Enter the filesystem path where AtoM should be installed (or where your
 existing AtoM installation is located for heratio-only mode).
 .
 Common paths: /usr/share/nginx/atom, /var/www/atom, /opt/atom

Template: atom-heratio/existing-atom-detected
Type: note
Description: Existing AtoM installation detected
 An existing AtoM installation was found at the specified path.
 .
 Detected version: ${ATOM_VERSION}
 .
 Heratio will be layered on top of this installation. Your existing
 data, database, and uploads will be preserved.

Template: atom-heratio/atom-version-too-old
Type: error
Description: AtoM version too old
 The existing AtoM installation is version ${ATOM_VERSION}, but Heratio
 requires AtoM >= 2.8.
 .
 Please upgrade your AtoM installation first, or choose "complete" mode
 to install a fresh AtoM 2.10 with Heratio.

Template: atom-heratio/db-host
Type: string
Default: localhost
Description: Database host:
 Enter the hostname or IP address of the MySQL/MariaDB server.

Template: atom-heratio/db-name
Type: string
Default: atom
Description: Database name:
 Enter the name of the database to use for AtoM. It will be created
 if it does not exist.

Template: atom-heratio/db-user
Type: string
Default: atom
Description: Database username:
 Enter the database username for AtoM to connect with. The user will
 be created if it does not exist.

Template: atom-heratio/db-password
Type: password
Description: Database password:
 Enter the password for the AtoM database user.
 .
 Minimum 8 characters recommended for production use.

Template: atom-heratio/db-root-password
Type: password
Description: MySQL root password:
 Enter the MySQL root password so the installer can create the database
 and user. Leave empty if MySQL allows passwordless root access (e.g.,
 via unix socket authentication).

Template: atom-heratio/site-title
Type: string
Default: My Archive
Description: Site title:
 Enter the title for your AtoM site. This appears in the browser title
 bar and site header.

Template: atom-heratio/site-url
Type: string
Description: Site URL:
 Enter the full URL for your AtoM site (e.g., https://archive.example.com).
 .
 If left empty, the server's IP address will be used with http://.

Template: atom-heratio/admin-email
Type: string
Description: Administrator email:
 Enter the email address for the AtoM administrator account.

Template: atom-heratio/admin-password
Type: password
Description: Administrator password:
 Set the password for the AtoM administrator account.
 .
 Minimum 8 characters required.

Template: atom-heratio/ssl-mode
Type: select
Choices: none, self-signed, letsencrypt
Default: none
Description: SSL/TLS configuration:
 Choose how to configure HTTPS for your AtoM site:
 .
  none        - HTTP only (configure SSL later)
  self-signed - Generate a self-signed certificate (for testing/internal use)
  letsencrypt - Obtain a free Let's Encrypt certificate (requires valid domain)

Template: atom-heratio/ssl-domain
Type: string
Description: Domain name for SSL certificate:
 Enter the domain name for the SSL certificate (e.g., archive.example.com).
 .
 For Let's Encrypt, this domain must already point to this server's IP.

Template: atom-heratio/elasticsearch-host
Type: string
Default: localhost:9200
Description: Elasticsearch host:port:
 Enter the Elasticsearch host and port. Elasticsearch is required for
 AtoM's full-text search functionality.

Template: atom-heratio/install-search
Type: boolean
Default: true
Description: Install Elasticsearch/OpenSearch?
 AtoM requires a search engine for full-text search. This option will
 install Elasticsearch 8.x and configure it for AtoM.
 .
 Choose YES for a new installation. Choose NO if you already have
 Elasticsearch or OpenSearch running, or want to configure it manually.

Template: atom-heratio/enable-web-wizard
Type: boolean
Default: true
Description: Launch web-based configuration wizard after install?
 The web wizard provides a browser-based interface for advanced
 configuration: plugin selection by category, GLAM sector setup,
 AI & automation, compliance modules, and preservation settings.
 .
 It runs temporarily on a separate port and auto-shuts down after
 30 minutes of inactivity. Access token is displayed after install.

Template: atom-heratio/web-wizard-port
Type: string
Default: 9090
Description: Web wizard port:
 Enter the port number for the web-based configuration wizard.
 Make sure this port is not in use by another service.
